# Force LF line endings on HTML/JS/CSS to keep CSP hash-based directives
# stable across Windows checkouts. Without this, Windows core.autocrlf=true
# (default for some installs) would convert LF → CRLF on checkout, changing
# byte content of inline <script>/<style> blocks → SHA-256 hash mismatch
# → CSP blocks the block → page renders broken.
#
# Added 2026-05-10 as part of CSP 'unsafe-inline' removal pass on
# collection/index.html. Applies to all text files in the repo so future
# expansion to app/about/index doesn't drift either.
* text=auto eol=lf
*.html text eol=lf
*.js text eol=lf
*.css text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
